## Business question

> *Can we reliably estimate how hotel price depends on distance from the city centre? When should we trust our regression output — and when should we not?*

Work through the tasks below in order. Each task asks you to build one or two diagnostic plots by hand before verifying with `check_model()`. By the end you should be able to read a diagnostic dashboard and know what each panel is actually computing.

---

## Setup


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
library(tidyverse)
library(broom)
library(modelsummary)
library(lmtest)
library(sandwich)
library(car)
library(performance)
library(see)
library(patchwork)

hotels <- read_csv("data/hotels_cs.csv", show_col_types = FALSE)
```
:::


Start with this baseline model. You will improve it step by step.


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
model_base <- lm(price ~ distance + stars, data = hotels)
```
:::


